%T A396251 133995520,536372352,2146364864,8587422720,34354131072,137426814976,
%U A396251 549729868928,2198968196096
%N A396251 a(n) is the number of 4-ary sequences of length n with characteristic value 0.
%C A396251 A 4-ary sequence is a sequence in which every term is 0, 1, 2 or 3.
%C A396251 Define the difference sequence of a 4-ary sequence (x(1), ..., x(n)) as (|x(1) - x(2)|, |x(2) - x(3)|, ..., |x(n-1) - x(n)|). The difference operation is similar to the Ducci game, except that there is no |x(n) - x(1)| term.
%C A396251 For a 4-ary sequence S of length n, take its difference sequence n-1 times, and the remaining number is the characteristic value of S.
%C A396251 There are 2*4^(n-1) 4-ary sequences with characteristic value 0 or 2, 2*4^(n-1) - 2^(n-1) 4-ary sequences with characteristic value 1, and 2^(n-1) 4-ary sequences with characteristic value 3.
%H A396251 Yifan Xie, <a href="/A396251/a396251_1.py.txt">Python program</a>
%e A396251 For n = 2, the a(2) = 4 sequences are (0, 0), (1, 1), (2, 2) and (3, 3).
%Y A396251 Cf. A396250, A396614.
